AUDIO: 'You just built a voice AI agent. It works. Then the bill shows up and you\'re paying for the LLM, the voice, the phone call, and then another platform fee on top of that. That\'s not even the worst part. The worst part, you still don\'t really even own the system. Today, I\'ll'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'show you Dogra, an open-source Vapi alternative you can self-host, inspect, and control. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Voice AI nowadays can look somewhat'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simple from the outside. Take a phone call, turn speech into text, send it to the LLM, turn the answer back into speech. It\'s done. That\'s easy, right? Well, as any of us know who have tried'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this, not really. Because real calls are messy. People interrupt, people go silent, they\'re going to change topics. They can ask really weird questions. Your agent needs to call APIs and when'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it breaks, you need to know why. That is where most voice AI projects become more of a pain. A voice agent is not just ChatGPT with a phone number. It is a live system with a bunch of moving'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'parts, right? That\'s speech-to-text, LLM, text-to-speech, state, tool calls, a boatload of other things. You get it. There\'s a lot of moving parts that we don\'t actually see happening. And when the call fails, the bot gave a bad'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'answer is not enough. Was it the prompt? Was it the model? What was it? Why did it fail? And this is where Dogra comes in. If you enjoy coding tools that speed up your workflow, be sure to subscribe. We have videos coming out all the time.'

